      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ranged Tactics Toolbox pg. 33</em>, <em>Adventurer's Armory pg. 2</em>, <em>Advanced Player's Guide pg. 176</em>, <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 21</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 3 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 3 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> 30 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> B; <strong>Special</strong> see text</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Ranged; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Thrown</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>The boomerang is primarily a hunting tool, but it is not uncommon for these versatile thrown weapons to be carried into battle. A boomerang is made of wood and is flat, with a long haft, a pronounced forward curve, and a sharp backward bend at the head. A hunting boomerang does not fly in a returning path.</p>"
